4262  ReduceIfReachableAbortCSADcheck(message);
4263  }
4264 
4265  // CatchBlockBegin should always be the 1st operation of a catch handler, and
4266  // returns the value of the exception that was caught. Because of split-edge
4267  // form, catch handlers cannot have multiple predecessors (since their
4268  // predecessors always end with CheckException, which has 2 successors). As
4269  // such, when multiple CheckException go to the same catch handler,
4270  // Assembler::AddPredecessor and Assembler::SplitEdge take care of introducing
4271  // additional intermediate catch handlers, which are then wired to the
4272  // original catch handler. When calling `__ CatchBlockBegin` at the begining
4273  // of the original catch handler, a Phi of the CatchBlockBegin of the
4274  // predecessors is emitted instead. Here is an example:
4275  //
4276  // Initial graph:
4277  //
4278  // + B1 ----------------+
4279  // | ... |
4280  // | 1: CallOp(...) |
4281  // | 2: CheckException |
4282  // +--------------------+
4283  // / \
4284  // / \
4285  // / \
4286  // + B2 ----------------+ + B3 ----------------+
4287  // | 3: DidntThrow(1) | | 4: CatchBlockBegin |
4288  // | ... | | 5: SomeOp(4) |
4289  // | ... | | ... |
4290  // +--------------------+ +--------------------+
4291  // \ /
4292  // \ /
4293  // \ /
4294  // + B4 ----------------+
4295  // | 6: Phi(3, 4) |
4296  // | ... |
4297  // +--------------------+
4298  //
4299  //
4300  // Let's say that we lower the CallOp to 2 throwing calls. We'll thus get:
4301  //
4302  //
4303  // + B1 ----------------+
4304  // | ... |
4305  // | 1: CallOp(...) |
4306  // | 2: CheckException |
4307  // +--------------------+
4308  // / \
4309  // / \
4310  // / \
4311  // + B2 ----------------+ + B4 ----------------+
4312  // | 3: DidntThrow(1) | | 7: CatchBlockBegin |
4313  // | 4: CallOp(...) | | 8: Goto(B6) |
4314  // | 5: CheckException | +--------------------+
4315  // +--------------------+ \
4316  // / \ \
4317  // / \ \
4318  // / \ \
4319  // + B3 ----------------+ + B5 ----------------+ |
4320  // | 6: DidntThrow(4) | | 9: CatchBlockBegin | |
4321  // | ... | | 10: Goto(B6) | |
4322  // | ... | +--------------------+ |
4323  // +--------------------+ \ |
4324  // \ \ |
4325  // \ \ |
4326  // \ + B6 ----------------+
4327  // \ | 11: Phi(7, 9) |
4328  // \ | 12: SomeOp(11) |
4329  // \ | ... |
4330  // \ +--------------------+
4331  // \ /
4332  // \ /
4333  // \ /
4334  // + B7 ----------------+
4335  // | 6: Phi(6, 11) |
4336  // | ... |
4337  // +--------------------+
4338  //
4339  // Note B6 in the output graph corresponds to B3 in the input graph and that
4340  // `11: Phi(7, 9)` was emitted when calling `CatchBlockBegin` in order to map
4341  // `4: CatchBlockBegin` from the input graph.
4342  //
4343  // Besides AddPredecessor and SplitEdge in Assembler, most of the machinery to
4344  // make this work is in GenericReducerBase (in particular,
4345  // `REDUCE(CatchBlockBegin)`, `REDUCE(Call)`, `REDUCE(CheckException)` and
4346  // `CatchIfInCatchScope`).
4347  V<Object> CatchBlockBegin() { return ReduceIfReachableCatchBlockBegin(); }
4348

4364  // Return `true` if the control flow after the conditional jump is reachable.
4365  ConditionalGotoStatus GotoIf(V<Word32> condition, Block* if_true,
4366  BranchHint hint = BranchHint::kNone) {
4367  if (V8_UNLIKELY(Asm().generating_unreachable_operations())) {
4368  // What we return here should not matter.
4369  return ConditionalGotoStatus::kBranch;
4370  }
4371  Block* if_false = Asm().NewBlock();
4372  return BranchAndBind(condition, if_true, if_false, hint, if_false);
4373  }
4374  ConditionalGotoStatus GotoIf(ConditionWithHint condition, Block* if_true) {
4375  return GotoIf(condition.condition(), if_true, condition.hint());
4376  }
4377  // Return `true` if the control flow after the conditional jump is reachable.
4378  ConditionalGotoStatus GotoIfNot(V<Word32> condition, Block* if_false,
4379  BranchHint hint = BranchHint::kNone) {
4380  if (V8_UNLIKELY(Asm().generating_unreachable_operations())) {
4381  // What we return here should not matter.
4382  return ConditionalGotoStatus::kBranch;
4383  }
4384  Block* if_true = Asm().NewBlock();
4385  return BranchAndBind(condition, if_true, if_false, hint, if_true);
4386  }
4387 
4388  ConditionalGotoStatus GotoIfNot(ConditionWithHint condition,
4389  Block* if_false) {
4390  return GotoIfNot(condition.condition(), if_false, condition.hint());
4391  }

4393  OpIndex CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, V<turboshaft::FrameState> frame_state,
4394  base::Vector<OpIndex> arguments, CanThrow can_throw,
4395  Isolate* isolate) {
4396  if (V8_UNLIKELY(Asm().generating_unreachable_operations())) {
4397  return OpIndex::Invalid();
4398  }
4399  Callable const callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate, builtin);
4400  Zone* graph_zone = Asm().output_graph().graph_zone();
4401 
4402  const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
4403  graph_zone, callable.descriptor(),
4404  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
4405  CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoThrow | Operator::kNoDeopt);
4406  DCHECK_EQ(call_descriptor->NeedsFrameState(), frame_state.valid());
4407 
4408  const TSCallDescriptor* ts_call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
4409  call_descriptor, can_throw, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, graph_zone);
4410 
4411  OpIndex callee = Asm().HeapConstant(callable.code());
4412 
4413  return Asm().Call(callee, frame_state, arguments, ts_call_descriptor);
4414  }

4447  // TODO(nicohartmann): Maybe this can be unified with Dcheck?
4448  void AssertImpl(V<Word32> condition, const char* condition_string,
4449  const char* file, int line) {
4450 #ifdef DEBUG
4451  // We use 256 characters as a buffer size. This can be increased if
4452  // necessary.
4453  static constexpr size_t kMaxAssertCommentLength = 256;
4454  base::Vector<char> buffer =
4455  Asm().data()->compilation_zone()->template AllocateVector<char>(
4456  kMaxAssertCommentLength);
4457  int result = base::SNPrintF(buffer, "Assert: %s [%s:%d]",
4458  condition_string, file, line);
4459  DCHECK_LT(0, result);
4460  Comment(buffer.data());
4461  IF_NOT (LIKELY(condition)) {
4462  Comment(buffer.data());
4463  Comment("ASSERT FAILED");
4464  DebugBreak();
4465  }
4466 
4467 #endif
4468  }

4484  void Comment(const char* message) { ReduceIfReachableComment(message); }
4485  void Comment(const std::string& message) {
4486  size_t length = message.length() + 1;
4487  char* zone_buffer =
4488  Asm().data()->compilation_zone()->template AllocateArray<char>(length);
4489  MemCopy(zone_buffer, message.c_str(), length);
4490  Comment(zone_buffer);
4491  }
4492  using MessageWithSourceLocation = CodeAssembler::MessageWithSourceLocation;
4493  template <typename... Args>
4494  void CodeComment(MessageWithSourceLocation message, Args&&... args) {
4495  if (!v8_flags.code_comments) return;
4496  std::ostringstream s;
4497  USE(s << message.message, (s << std::forward<Args>(args))...);
4498  if (message.loc.FileName()) {
4499  s << " - " << message.loc.ToString();
4500  }
4501  Comment(std::move(s).str());
4502  }

4801  V<Object> LoadRoot(RootIndex root_index) {
4802  Isolate* isolate = __ data() -> isolate();
4803  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate);
4804  if (RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(root_index)) {
4805  Handle<Object> root = isolate->root_handle(root_index);
4806  if (i::IsSmi(*root)) {
4807  return __ SmiConstant(Cast<Smi>(*root));
4808  } else {
4809  return HeapConstantMaybeHole(i::Cast<HeapObject>(root));
4810  }
4811  }
4812 
4813  // TODO(jgruber): In theory we could generate better code for this by
4814  // letting the macro assembler decide how to load from the roots list. In
4815  // most cases, it would boil down to loading from a fixed kRootRegister
4816  // offset.
4817  OpIndex isolate_root =
4818  __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_root(isolate));
4819  int offset = IsolateData::root_slot_offset(root_index);
4820  return __ LoadOffHeap(isolate_root, offset,
4821  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged());
4822  }
4823 
4824 #define HEAP_CONSTANT_ACCESSOR(rootIndexName, rootAccessorName, name) \
4825  V<RemoveTagged< \
4826  decltype(std::declval<ReadOnlyRoots>().rootAccessorName())>::type> \
4827  name##Constant() { \
4828  const TurboshaftPipelineKind kind = __ data() -> pipeline_kind(); \
4829  if (V8_UNLIKELY(kind == TurboshaftPipelineKind::kCSA || \
4830  kind == TurboshaftPipelineKind::kTSABuiltin)) { \
4831  DCHECK(RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(RootIndex::k##rootIndexName)); \
4832  return V<RemoveTagged< \
4833  decltype(std::declval<ReadOnlyRoots>().rootAccessorName())>::type>:: \
4834  Cast(__ LoadRoot(RootIndex::k##rootIndexName)); \
4835  } else { \
4836  Isolate* isolate = __ data() -> isolate(); \
4837  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate); \
4838  Factory* factory = isolate->factory(); \
4839  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(factory); \
4840  return __ HeapConstant(factory->rootAccessorName()); \
4841  } \
4842  }
4843  HEAP_IMMUTABLE_IMMOVABLE_OBJECT_LIST(HEAP_CONSTANT_ACCESSOR)
4844 #undef HEAP_CONSTANT_ACCESSOR
4845 
4846 #define HEAP_CONSTANT_ACCESSOR(rootIndexName, rootAccessorName, name) \
4847  V<RemoveTagged<decltype(std::declval<Heap>().rootAccessorName())>::type> \
4848  name##Constant() { \
4849  const TurboshaftPipelineKind kind = __ data() -> pipeline_kind(); \
4850  if (V8_UNLIKELY(kind == TurboshaftPipelineKind::kCSA || \
4851  kind == TurboshaftPipelineKind::kTSABuiltin)) { \
4852  DCHECK(RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(RootIndex::k##rootIndexName)); \
4853  return V< \
4854  RemoveTagged<decltype(std::declval<Heap>().rootAccessorName())>:: \
4855  type>::Cast(__ LoadRoot(RootIndex::k##rootIndexName)); \
4856  } else { \
4857  Isolate* isolate = __ data() -> isolate(); \
4858  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate); \
4859  Factory* factory = isolate->factory(); \
4860  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(factory); \
4861  return __ HeapConstant(factory->rootAccessorName()); \
4862  } \
4863  }
4864  HEAP_MUTABLE_IMMOVABLE_OBJECT_LIST(HEAP_CONSTANT_ACCESSOR)
4865 #undef HEAP_CONSTANT_ACCESSOR
4866 
4867 #define HEAP_CONSTANT_TEST(rootIndexName, rootAccessorName, name) \
4868  V<Word32> Is##name(V<Object> value) { \
4869  return TaggedEqual(value, name##Constant()); \
4870  } \
4871  V<Word32> IsNot##name(V<Object> value) { \
4872  return TaggedNotEqual(value, name##Constant()); \
4873  }
4874  HEAP_IMMOVABLE_OBJECT_LIST(HEAP_CONSTANT_TEST)
4875 #undef HEAP_CONSTANT_TEST

5211  private:
5212 #ifdef DEBUG
5213 #define REDUCE_OP(Op) \
5214  template <class... Args> \
5215  V8_INLINE OpIndex ReduceIfReachable##Op(Args... args) { \
5216  if (V8_UNLIKELY(Asm().generating_unreachable_operations())) { \
5217  DCHECK(Asm().conceptually_in_a_block()); \
5218  return OpIndex::Invalid(); \
5219  } \
5220  OpIndex result = Asm().Reduce##Op(args...); \
5221  if constexpr (!IsBlockTerminator(Opcode::k##Op)) { \
5222  if (Asm().current_block() == nullptr) { \
5223  /* The input operation was not a block terminator, but a reducer \
5224  * lowered it into a block terminator. */ \
5225  Asm().set_conceptually_in_a_block(true); \
5226  } \
5227  } \
5228  return result; \
5229  }
5230 #else
5231 #define REDUCE_OP(Op) \
5232  template <class... Args> \
5233  V8_INLINE OpIndex ReduceIfReachable##Op(Args... args) { \
5234  if (V8_UNLIKELY(Asm().generating_unreachable_operations())) { \
5235  return OpIndex::Invalid(); \
5236  } \
5237  /* With an empty reducer stack, `Asm().Reduce##Op` will just create a */ \
5238  /* new `Op` operation (defined in operations.h). To figure out where */ \
5239  /* this operation is lowered or optimized (if anywhere), search for */ \
5240  /* `REDUCE(<your operation>)`. Then, to know when this lowering */ \
5241  /* actually happens, search for phases that are instantiated with */ \
5242  /* that reducer. You can also look in operation.h where the opcode is */ \
5243  /* declared: operations declared in */ \
5244  /* TURBOSHAFT_SIMPLIFIED_OPERATION_LIST are typically lowered in */ \
5245  /* machine-lowering-reducer-inl.h, and operations in */ \
5246  /* TURBOSHAFT_MACHINE_OPERATION_LIST are typically not lowered before */ \
5247  /* reaching instruction-selector.h. */ \
5248  return Asm().Reduce##Op(args...); \
5249  }
5250 #endif
5251  TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(REDUCE_OP)
5252 #undef REDUCE_OP
5253 
5254  // LoadArrayBufferElement and LoadNonArrayBufferElement should be called
5255  // instead of LoadElement.
5256  template <typename T = Any, typename Base>
5257  V<T> LoadElement(V<Base> object, const ElementAccess& access,
5258  V<WordPtr> index, bool is_array_buffer) {
5259  if constexpr (is_taggable_v<Base>) {
5260  DCHECK_EQ(access.base_is_tagged, BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase);
5261  } else {
5262  static_assert(std::is_same_v<Base, WordPtr>);
5263  DCHECK_EQ(access.base_is_tagged, BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase);
5264  }
5265  LoadOp::Kind kind = LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(access.base_is_tagged);
5266  if (is_array_buffer) kind = kind.NotLoadEliminable();
5267  MemoryRepresentation rep =
5268  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineType(access.machine_type);
5269  return Load(object, index, kind, rep, access.header_size,
5270  rep.SizeInBytesLog2());
5271  }
5272 
5273  // StoreArrayBufferElement and StoreNonArrayBufferElement should be called
5274  // instead of StoreElement.
5275  template <typename Base>
5276  void StoreElement(V<Base> object, const ElementAccess& access,
5277  ConstOrV<WordPtr> index, V<Any> value,
5278  bool is_array_buffer) {
5279  if constexpr (is_taggable_v<Base>) {
5280  DCHECK_EQ(access.base_is_tagged, BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase);
5281  } else {
5282  static_assert(std::is_same_v<Base, WordPtr>);
5283  DCHECK_EQ(access.base_is_tagged, BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase);
5284  }
5285  LoadOp::Kind kind = LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(access.base_is_tagged);
5286  if (is_array_buffer) kind = kind.NotLoadEliminable();
5287  MemoryRepresentation rep =
5288  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineType(access.machine_type);
5289  Store(object, resolve(index), value, kind, rep, access.write_barrier_kind,
5290  access.header_size, rep.SizeInBytesLog2());
5291  }
5292 
5293  // BranchAndBind should be called from GotoIf/GotoIfNot. It will insert a
5294  // Branch, bind {to_bind} (which should correspond to the implicit new block
5295  // following the GotoIf/GotoIfNot) and return a ConditionalGotoStatus
5296  // representing whether the destinations of the Branch are reachable or not.
5297  ConditionalGotoStatus BranchAndBind(V<Word32> condition, Block* if_true,
5298  Block* if_false, BranchHint hint,
5299  Block* to_bind) {
5300  DCHECK_EQ(to_bind, any_of(if_true, if_false));
5301  Block* other = to_bind == if_true ? if_false : if_true;
5302  Block* to_bind_last_pred = to_bind->LastPredecessor();
5303  Block* other_last_pred = other->LastPredecessor();
5304  Asm().Branch(condition, if_true, if_false, hint);
5305  bool to_bind_reachable = to_bind_last_pred != to_bind->LastPredecessor();
5306  bool other_reachable = other_last_pred != other->LastPredecessor();
5307  ConditionalGotoStatus status = static_cast<ConditionalGotoStatus>(
5308  static_cast<int>(other_reachable) | ((to_bind_reachable) << 1));
5309  bool bind_status = Asm().Bind(to_bind);
5310  DCHECK_EQ(bind_status, to_bind_reachable);
5311  USE(bind_status);
5312  return status;
5313  }
5314 
5315  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> cached_parameters_;
5316  // [0] contains the stub with exit frame.
5317  MaybeHandle<Code> cached_centry_stub_constants_[4];
5318  bool in_object_initialization_ = false;
5319 
5320  OperationMatcher matcher_;
5321 };

5323 // Some members of Assembler that are used in the constructors of the stack are
5324 // extracted to the AssemblerData class, so that they can be initialized before
5325 // the rest of the stack, and thus don't need to be passed as argument to all of
5326 // the constructors of the stack.
5327 struct AssemblerData {
5328  // TODO(dmercadier): consider removing input_graph from this, and only having
5329  // it in GraphVisitor for Stacks that have it.
5330  AssemblerData(PipelineData* data, Graph& input_graph, Graph& output_graph,
5331  Zone* phase_zone)
5332  : data(data),
5333  phase_zone(phase_zone),
5334  input_graph(input_graph),
5335  output_graph(output_graph) {}
5336  PipelineData* data;
5337  Zone* phase_zone;
5338  Graph& input_graph;
5339  Graph& output_graph;
5340 };
5341 
5342 template <class Reducers>
5343 class Assembler : public AssemblerData,
5344  public ReducerStack<Reducers>::type,
5345  public TurboshaftAssemblerOpInterface<Assembler<Reducers>> {
5346  using Stack = typename ReducerStack<Reducers>::type;
5347  using node_t = typename Stack::node_t;
5348 
5349  public:
5350  explicit Assembler(PipelineData* data, Graph& input_graph,
5351  Graph& output_graph, Zone* phase_zone)
5352  : AssemblerData(data, input_graph, output_graph, phase_zone), Stack() {
5353  SupportedOperations::Initialize();
5354  }
5355 
5356  using Stack::Asm;
5357 
5358  PipelineData* data() const { return AssemblerData::data; }
5359  Zone* phase_zone() { return AssemblerData::phase_zone; }
5360  const Graph& input_graph() const { return AssemblerData::input_graph; }
5361  Graph& output_graph() const { return AssemblerData::output_graph; }
5362  Zone* graph_zone() const { return output_graph().graph_zone(); }
5363 
5364  // When analyzers detect that an operation is dead, they replace its opcode by
5365  // kDead in-place, and thus need to have a non-const input graph.
5366  Graph& modifiable_input_graph() const { return AssemblerData::input_graph; }
5367 
5368  Block* NewLoopHeader() { return this->output_graph().NewLoopHeader(); }
5369  Block* NewBlock() { return this->output_graph().NewBlock(); }
5370 
5371 // This condition is true for any compiler except GCC.
5372 #if defined(__clang__) || !defined(V8_CC_GNU)
5373  V8_INLINE
5374 #endif
5375  bool Bind(Block* block) {
5376 #ifdef DEBUG
5377  set_conceptually_in_a_block(true);
5378 #endif
5379 
5380  if (block->IsLoop() && block->single_loop_predecessor()) {
5381  // {block} is a loop header that had multiple incoming forward edges, and
5382  // for which we've created a "single_predecessor" block. We bind it now,
5383  // and insert a single Goto to the original loop header.
5384  BindReachable(block->single_loop_predecessor());
5385  // We need to go through a raw Emit because calling this->Goto would go
5386  // through AddPredecessor and SplitEdge, which would wrongly try to
5387  // prevent adding more predecessors to the loop header.
5388  this->template Emit<GotoOp>(block, /*is_backedge*/ false);
5389  }
5390 
5391  if (!this->output_graph().Add(block)) {
5392  return false;
5393  }
5394  DCHECK_NULL(current_block_);
5395  current_block_ = block;
5396  Stack::Bind(block);
5397  return true;
5398  }
5399 
5400  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Remove this.
5401  V8_INLINE void BindReachable(Block* block) {
5402  bool bound = Bind(block);
5403  DCHECK(bound);
5404  USE(bound);
5405  }
5406 
5407  // Every loop should be finalized once, after it is certain that no backedge
5408  // can be added anymore.
5409  void FinalizeLoop(Block* loop_header) {
5410  if (loop_header->IsLoop() && loop_header->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
5411  this->output_graph().TurnLoopIntoMerge(loop_header);
5412  }
5413  }

5416  current_operation_origin_ = operation_origin;
5417  }

5421  conceptually_in_a_block_ = value;
5422  }
5423  bool conceptually_in_a_block() { return conceptually_in_a_block_; }
5424 #endif
5425 
5426  Block* current_block() const { return current_block_; }
5427  bool generating_unreachable_operations() const {
5428  return current_block() == nullptr;
5429  }
5430  V<AnyOrNone> current_operation_origin() const {
5431  return current_operation_origin_;
5432  }

5435  return this->output_graph().Get(op_idx);
5436  }

5439  // CatchScope should be used in most cases to set the current catch block, but
5440  // this is sometimes impractical.
5441  void set_current_catch_block(Block* block) { current_catch_block_ = block; }

5445 #endif
5446 
5447  // ReduceProjection eliminates projections to tuples and returns the
5448  // corresponding tuple input instead. We do this at the top of the stack to
5449  // avoid passing this Projection around needlessly. This is in particular
5450  // important to ValueNumberingReducer, which assumes that it's at the bottom
5451  // of the stack, and that the BaseReducer will actually emit an Operation. If
5452  // we put this projection-to-tuple-simplification in the BaseReducer, then
5453  // this assumption of the ValueNumberingReducer will break.
5454  V<Any> ReduceProjection(V<Any> tuple, uint16_t index,
5455  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
5456  if (auto* tuple_op = Asm().matcher().template TryCast<TupleOp>(tuple)) {
5457  return tuple_op->input(index);
5458  }
5459  return Stack::ReduceProjection(tuple, index, rep);
5460  }
5461 
5462  // Adds {source} to the predecessors of {destination}.
5463  void AddPredecessor(Block* source, Block* destination, bool branch) {
5464  DCHECK_IMPLIES(branch, source->EndsWithBranchingOp(this->output_graph()));
5465  if (destination->LastPredecessor() == nullptr) {
5466  // {destination} has currently no predecessors.
5467  DCHECK(destination->IsLoopOrMerge());
5468  if (branch && destination->IsLoop()) {
5469  // We always split Branch edges that go to loop headers.
5470  SplitEdge(source, destination);
5471  } else {
5472  destination->AddPredecessor(source);
5473  if (branch) {
5474  DCHECK(!destination->IsLoop());
5475  destination->SetKind(Block::Kind::kBranchTarget);
5476  }
5477  }
5478  return;
5479  } else if (destination->IsBranchTarget()) {
5480  // {destination} used to be a BranchTarget, but branch targets can only
5481  // have one predecessor. We'll thus split its (single) incoming edge, and
5482  // change its type to kMerge.
5483  DCHECK_EQ(destination->PredecessorCount(), 1);
5484  Block* pred = destination->LastPredecessor();
5485  destination->ResetLastPredecessor();
5486  destination->SetKind(Block::Kind::kMerge);
5487  // We have to split `pred` first to preserve order of predecessors.
5488  SplitEdge(pred, destination);
5489  if (branch) {
5490  // A branch always goes to a BranchTarget. We thus split the edge: we'll
5491  // insert a new Block, to which {source} will branch, and which will
5492  // "Goto" to {destination}.
5493  SplitEdge(source, destination);
5494  } else {
5495  // {destination} is a Merge, and {source} just does a Goto; nothing
5496  // special to do.
5497  destination->AddPredecessor(source);
5498  }
5499  return;
5500  }
5501 
5502  DCHECK(destination->IsLoopOrMerge());
5503 
5504  if (destination->IsLoop() && !destination->IsBound()) {
5505  DCHECK(!branch);
5506  DCHECK_EQ(destination->PredecessorCount(), 1);
5507  // We are trying to add an additional forward edge to this loop, which is
5508  // not allowed (all loops in Turboshaft should have exactly one incoming
5509  // forward edge). Instead, we'll create a new predecessor for the loop,
5510  // where all previous and future forward predecessors will be routed to.
5511  Block* single_predecessor =
5512  destination->single_loop_predecessor()
5513  ? destination->single_loop_predecessor()
5514  : CreateSinglePredecessorForLoop(destination);
5515  AddLoopPredecessor(single_predecessor, source);
5516  return;
5517  }
5518 
5519  if (branch) {
5520  // A branch always goes to a BranchTarget. We thus split the edge: we'll
5521  // insert a new Block, to which {source} will branch, and which will
5522  // "Goto" to {destination}.
5523  SplitEdge(source, destination);
5524  } else {
5525  // {destination} is a Merge, and {source} just does a Goto; nothing
5526  // special to do.
5527  destination->AddPredecessor(source);
5528  }
5529  }
5530 
5531  private:
5532  void FinalizeBlock() {
5533  this->output_graph().Finalize(current_block_);
5534  current_block_ = nullptr;
5535 #ifdef DEBUG
5536  set_conceptually_in_a_block(false);
5537 #endif
5538  }
5539 
5540  Block* CreateSinglePredecessorForLoop(Block* loop_header) {
5541  DCHECK(loop_header->IsLoop());
5542  DCHECK(!loop_header->IsBound());
5543  DCHECK_EQ(loop_header->PredecessorCount(), 1);
5544 
5545  Block* old_predecessor = loop_header->LastPredecessor();
5546  // Because we always split edges going to loop headers, we know that
5547  // {predecessor} ends with a Goto.
5548  GotoOp& old_predecessor_goto =
5549  old_predecessor->LastOperation(this->output_graph())
5550  .template Cast<GotoOp>();
5551 
5552  Block* single_loop_predecessor = NewBlock();
5553  single_loop_predecessor->SetKind(Block::Kind::kMerge);
5554  single_loop_predecessor->SetOrigin(loop_header->OriginForLoopHeader());
5555 
5556  // Re-routing the final Goto of {old_predecessor} to go to
5557  // {single_predecessor} instead of {loop_header}.
5558  single_loop_predecessor->AddPredecessor(old_predecessor);
5559  old_predecessor_goto.destination = single_loop_predecessor;
5560 
5561  // Resetting the predecessors of {loop_header}: it will now have a single
5562  // predecessor, {old_predecessor}, which isn't bound yet. (and which will be
5563  // bound automatically in Bind)
5564  loop_header->ResetAllPredecessors();
5565  loop_header->AddPredecessor(single_loop_predecessor);
5566  loop_header->SetSingleLoopPredecessor(single_loop_predecessor);
5567 
5568  return single_loop_predecessor;
5569  }
5570 
5571  void AddLoopPredecessor(Block* single_predecessor, Block* new_predecessor) {
5572  GotoOp& new_predecessor_goto =
5573  new_predecessor->LastOperation(this->output_graph())
5574  .template Cast<GotoOp>();
5575  new_predecessor_goto.destination = single_predecessor;
5576  single_predecessor->AddPredecessor(new_predecessor);
5577  }
5578 
5579  // Insert a new Block between {source} and {destination}, in order to maintain
5580  // the split-edge form.
5581  void SplitEdge(Block* source, Block* destination) {
5582  DCHECK(source->EndsWithBranchingOp(this->output_graph()));
5583  // Creating the new intermediate block
5584  Block* intermediate_block = NewBlock();
5585  intermediate_block->SetKind(Block::Kind::kBranchTarget);
5586  // Updating "predecessor" edge of {intermediate_block}. This needs to be
5587  // done before calling Bind, because otherwise Bind will think that this
5588  // block is not reachable.
5589  intermediate_block->AddPredecessor(source);
5590 
5591  // Updating {source}'s last Branch/Switch/CheckException. Note that
5592  // this must be done before Binding {intermediate_block}, otherwise,
5593  // Reducer::Bind methods will see an invalid block being bound (because its
5594  // predecessor would be a branch, but none of its targets would be the block
5595  // being bound).
5596  Operation& op = this->output_graph().Get(
5597  this->output_graph().PreviousIndex(source->end()));
5598  switch (op.opcode) {
5599  case Opcode::kBranch: {
5600  BranchOp& branch = op.Cast<BranchOp>();
5601  if (branch.if_true == destination) {
5602  branch.if_true = intermediate_block;
5603  // We enforce that Branches if_false and if_true can never be the same
5604  // (there is a DCHECK in Assembler::Branch enforcing that).
5605  DCHECK_NE(branch.if_false, destination);
5606  } else {
5607  DCHECK_EQ(branch.if_false, destination);
5608  branch.if_false = intermediate_block;
5609  }
5610  break;
5611  }
5612  case Opcode::kCheckException: {
5613  CheckExceptionOp& catch_exception_op = op.Cast<CheckExceptionOp>();
5614  if (catch_exception_op.didnt_throw_block == destination) {
5615  catch_exception_op.didnt_throw_block = intermediate_block;
5616  // We assume that CheckException's successor and catch_block
5617  // can never be the same (there is a DCHECK in
5618  // CheckExceptionOp::Validate enforcing that).
5619  DCHECK_NE(catch_exception_op.catch_block, destination);
5620  } else {
5621  DCHECK_EQ(catch_exception_op.catch_block, destination);
5622  catch_exception_op.catch_block = intermediate_block;
5623  // A catch block always has to start with a `CatchBlockBeginOp`.
5624  BindReachable(intermediate_block);
5625  intermediate_block->SetOrigin(source->OriginForBlockEnd());
5626  this->CatchBlockBegin();
5627  this->Goto(destination);
5628  return;
5629  }
5630  break;
5631  }
5632  case Opcode::kSwitch: {
5633  SwitchOp& switch_op = op.Cast<SwitchOp>();
5634  bool found = false;
5635  for (auto& case_block : switch_op.cases) {
5636  if (case_block.destination == destination) {
5637  case_block.destination = intermediate_block;
5638  DCHECK(!found);
5639  found = true;
5640 #ifndef DEBUG
5641  break;
5642 #endif
5643  }
5644  }
5645  DCHECK_IMPLIES(found, switch_op.default_case != destination);
5646  if (!found) {
5647  DCHECK_EQ(switch_op.default_case, destination);
5648  switch_op.default_case = intermediate_block;
5649  }
5650  break;
5651  }
5652 
5653  default:
5654  UNREACHABLE();
5655  }
5656 
5657  BindReachable(intermediate_block);
5658  intermediate_block->SetOrigin(source->OriginForBlockEnd());
5659  // Inserting a Goto in {intermediate_block} to {destination}. This will
5660  // create the edge from {intermediate_block} to {destination}. Note that
5661  // this will call AddPredecessor, but we've already removed the possible
5662  // edge of {destination} that need splitting, so no risks of infinite
5663  // recursion here.
5664  this->Goto(destination);
5665  }
5666 
5667  Block* current_block_ = nullptr;
5668  Block* current_catch_block_ = nullptr;
5669 
5670  // `current_block_` is nullptr after emitting a block terminator and before
5671  // Binding the next block. During this time, emitting an operation doesn't do
5672  // anything (because in which block would it be emitted?). However, we also
5673  // want to prevent silently skipping operations because of a missing Bind.
5674  // Consider for instance a lowering that would do:
5675  //
5676  // __ Add(x, y)
5677  // __ Goto(B)
5678  // __ Add(i, j)
5679  //
5680  // The 2nd Add is unreachable, but this has to be a mistake, since we exitted
5681  // the current block before emitting it, and forgot to Bind a new block.
5682  // On the other hand, consider this:
5683  //
5684  // __ Add(x, y)
5685  // __ Goto(B1)
5686  // __ Bind(B2)
5687  // __ Add(i, j)
5688  //
5689  // It's possible that B2 is not reachable, in which case `Bind(B2)` will set
5690  // the current_block to nullptr.
5691  // Similarly, consider:
5692  //
5693  // __ Add(x, y)
5694  // __ DeoptimizeIf(cond)
5695  // __ Add(i, j)
5696  //
5697  // It's possible that a reducer lowers the `DeoptimizeIf` to an unconditional
5698  // `Deoptimize`.
5699  //
5700  // The 1st case should produce an error (because a Bind was forgotten), but
5701  // the 2nd and 3rd case should not.
5702  //
5703  // The way we achieve this is with the following `conceptually_in_a_block_`
5704  // boolean:
5705  // - when Binding a block (successfully or not), we set
5706  // `conceptually_in_a_block_` to true.
5707  // - when exiting a block (= emitting a block terminator), we set
5708  // `conceptually_in_a_block_` to false.
5709  // - after the AssemblerOpInterface lowers a non-block-terminator which
5710  // makes the current_block_ become nullptr (= the last operation of its
5711  // lowering became a block terminator), we set `conceptually_in_a_block_` to
5712  // true (overriding the "false" that was set when emitting the block
5713  // terminator).
5714  //
5715  // Note that there is one category of errors that this doesn't prevent: if a
5716  // lowering of a non-block terminator creates new control flow and forgets a
5717  // final Bind, we'll set `conceptually_in_a_block_` to true and assume that
5718  // this lowering unconditionally exits the control flow. However, it's hard to
5719  // distinguish between lowerings that voluntarily end with block terminators,
5720  // and those who forgot a Bind.
5721  bool conceptually_in_a_block_ = false;
5722 
5723  // TODO(dmercadier,tebbi): remove {current_operation_origin_} and pass instead
5724  // additional parameters to ReduceXXX methods.
5725  V<AnyOrNone> current_operation_origin_ = V<AnyOrNone>::Invalid();
5726 
5727 #ifdef DEBUG
5728  int intermediate_tracing_depth_ = 0;
5729 #endif
5730 
5731  template <class Next>
5732  friend class TSReducerBase;
5733  template <class AssemblerT>
5734  friend class CatchScopeImpl;
5735 };
5736 
5737 template <class AssemblerT>
5738 class CatchScopeImpl {
5739  public:
5740  CatchScopeImpl(AssemblerT& assembler, Block* catch_block)
5741  : assembler_(assembler),
5742  previous_catch_block_(assembler.current_catch_block_) {
5743  assembler_.current_catch_block_ = catch_block;
5744 #ifdef DEBUG
5745  this->catch_block = catch_block;
5746 #endif
5747  }
5748 
5749  ~CatchScopeImpl() {
5750  DCHECK_EQ(assembler_.current_catch_block_, catch_block);
5751  assembler_.current_catch_block_ = previous_catch_block_;
5752  }
5753 
5754  CatchScopeImpl& operator=(const CatchScopeImpl&) = delete;
5755  CatchScopeImpl(const CatchScopeImpl&) = delete;
5756  CatchScopeImpl& operator=(CatchScopeImpl&&) = delete;
5757  CatchScopeImpl(CatchScopeImpl&&) = delete;
5758 
5759  private:
5760  AssemblerT& assembler_;
5761  Block* previous_catch_block_;
5762 #ifdef DEBUG
5763  Block* catch_block = nullptr;
5764 #endif
5765 
5766  template <class Reducers>
5767  friend class Assembler;
5768 };
5769 
5770 template <template <class> class... Reducers>
5771 class TSAssembler : public Assembler<reducer_list<Reducers..., TSReducerBase>> {
5772  public:
5773  using Assembler<reducer_list<Reducers..., TSReducerBase>>::Assembler;
5774 };
